Grammy award-winning singer Burna Boy has put a big smile on the face of Hyzah, an upcoming singer, by gifting him $3000 (over N1.2m). In a viral video posted on Hyzah’s page, the upcoming singer prostrated before ‘Odogwu’ by lying completely flat on the ground, held on to his right foot and kissed it. Burna then requested he stand up and follow him. In another video, Hyzah was seen in the studio with Burna and a few other people as he entertained them. As he freestyled, the “Twice as Tall” singer nodded his head. - Advertisement -   We want to know who owns the oil     Navy alerts public on fraudulent recruitment websites     Singer Portable threatens to seduce married women   In yet another video, the youngster revealed Burna Boy gifted him $3000 after their meeting while displaying the mint. He appreciated Burna and showered him with prayers. The thrilled Hyzah said: “Burna boy bo card fun mi. Ah han! 3K dolz no be small thing o!” Next, he went on his knees and continued: “Baba thank you. Anybody wey dey hate you, na mumu hin be.” The video’s caption read: “What a way to start a new year. “I met the African Giant and got his blessings. More greatness Odogwu.”